ef="https://www.fulltable.com/iso/mw.htm" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;fulltable.com/iso/mw.htm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/992/593/862/235/561/original/43dc039ad76ed824.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/992/593/862/235/561/original/43dc039ad76ed824.jpg" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111994741148427788</guid><pubDate>Sun, 25 Feb 2024 23:35:30 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Benjamin Judkewitz</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@benjulab/111999662087772861</link><description>How can the tiny glassfish Danionella cerebrum, just over 1 cm long, produce high-amplitude communication sounds exceeding 140 dB? We found that it uses a fascinating drumming mechanism involving acceleration at over 2000 g:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.pnas.org/doi/10.1073/pnas.2314017121" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;pnas.org/doi/10.1073/pnas.2314&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;017121&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;1/10x slo-mo video has sound&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/111/999/658/973/104/910/original/d5b44983bb82409f.mp4"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/media_attachments/files/111/999/658/973/104/910/original/d5b44983bb82409f.mp4" alt="Mastodon video" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111999662087772861</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 20:26:58 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Marc Dubuisson</title><link>https://piaille.fr/@unpied/111997561870181233</link><description>Eh oui, les profs aussi ont une vie en dehors de l'√©cole !‚û°Ô∏è Mon tout nouveau recueil de strips est enfin sorti en librairie et commandable en ligne sur &lt;a href="https://www.exemplaire-editions.fr/librairie/livre/en-attendant-la-fin-du-monde-tome-deux" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;exemplaire-editions.fr/librair&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ie/livre/en-attendant-la-fin-du-monde-tome-deux&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/997/561/930/795/007/original/5b8d0bbf7d689961.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/997/561/930/795/007/original/5b8d0bbf7d689961.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111999784139645382</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 20:58:01 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/112000044336745558</link><description>&lt;a href="https://www.science.org/content/article/after-misconduct-claims-star-botanist-has-second-paper-retracted" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;science.org/content/article/af&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;ter-misconduct-claims-star-botanist-has-second-paper-retracted&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112000044336745558</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 22:04:11 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Spencer LaVere Smith</title><link>https://neuromatch.social/@sls/112000135440905004</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://fediscience.org/@tyrell_turing" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;tyrell_turing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mstdn.science/@cian" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;cian&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Agreed. Math and physics articles are often poor too. Textbooks still have a role to play.One exception is anything to do with telescopes and amateur astronomy. That community is wonderful. Top quality technical content. Organized, coherent, and up-to-date.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112000135598486548</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 22:27:21 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>PsychoPy</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@psychopy/112003337051680630</link><description>Did you know we have a library of surveys on Pavlovia.org? Here's a quick video on how to navigate to it!&lt;a href="https://buff.ly/49tsn0K" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;buff.ly/49tsn0K&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112003337051680630</guid><pubDate>Tue, 27 Feb 2024 12:01:34 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/112003388010804972</link><description>Dynamic Network Connectivity: from monkeys to humans&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnhum.2024.1353043/full" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://www.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;frontiersin.org/articles/10.33&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;89/fnhum.2024.1353043/full&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">112003388085029611</guid><pubDate>Tue, 27 Feb 2024 12:14:31 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title>